modules.description: This module manages SSL/TLS contexts for secure network communication. It provides functions to create and manipulate SSL contexts, retrieve associated file descriptors and sockets, and interface with underlying `Ssl` library types. Concrete use cases include setting up secure client-server connections and handling encrypted data transfer over streams.

This module implements TLS-secured network communication using `Eio_unix.Net.stream_socket` file descriptors. It provides `accept` and `connect` operations to establish encrypted client-server connections, enabling secure data transfer over streams. Concrete use cases include implementing HTTPS servers and clients with TLS encryption.
